  },
  {
    "id": "knpc2016-q109",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "programming",
    "subtopic": "cpp-streams",
    "stem": "Which of the following is false about cin?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "It represents a standard input",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "It is an object of stream class",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "It is a class of which stream is an object",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "Using cin the data can be read from user terminal",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "C"
    ],
    "explanation": "The question asks which statement is FALSE. In C++, cin is an object of the class istream, tied to standard input; it is not itself a class, so C reverses the relationship and is the false statement. A, B and D are all true descriptions of cin.",
    "source": {
